The critical issue is that `sc->stts_count` gets set at line 714, but then at line 898-899, the code checks `sc->stts_count && i < sc->tts_count` - it never validates that `sc->tts_data` itself is allocated. Since `sc->tts_count` could be 0 or have a value, but `sc->tts_data` remains uninitialized, dereferencing `sc->tts_data[i]` or `sc->tts_data[0]` will cause a NULL pointer dereference.

